<item>
            <title>[LU-16181] validate_lod_and_idx() message is missing information</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16181</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We&apos;ve seen errors like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;validate_lod_and_idx() fs-MDT0001: bad idx 103 of 32&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; in cases where there are sparse OST index numbers (e.g. OST index 0-15, 100-115 in use).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Firstly, the message doesn&apos;t print anything about the actual file FID that is having this problem, which should be done in &lt;tt&gt;lod_initialize_objects()&lt;/tt&gt; if &lt;tt&gt;validate_lod_and_idx()&lt;/tt&gt; returns an error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Secondly, the problem itself shouldn&apos;t happen.  I suspect it relates to the sparse vs. dense OST index being checked.  &lt;tt&gt;ltd_tgts_size&lt;/tt&gt; is the size of the &lt;tt&gt;ltd_tgt_idx[]&lt;/tt&gt; array, but not necessarily the maximum index in the array.  &lt;tt&gt;lod_initialize_objects()&lt;/tt&gt; is calling this function with &lt;tt&gt;l_ost_idx&lt;/tt&gt;, which &lt;em&gt;appears&lt;/em&gt; to be correct (&quot;&lt;tt&gt;/&amp;#42; OST index in LOV (lov_tgt_desc-&amp;gt;tgts) &amp;#42;/&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; but is clearly not in some cases. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
